{
  "texts": [
    "Upon further investigation, it was observed that the readability scores displayed weak to moderate correlations with the three ChatGPT-4 scores (see Table 5).",
    "More specifically, abstracts that received higher scores on the Accessibility and Understandability component were associated with higher readability scores (ρ up to -0.21), while abstracts that achieved higher scores in Novelty and Engagement received lower readability scores (ρ up to 0.28).",
    "Moreover, articles with a higher number of authors had higher Quality and Reliability scores (ρ = 0.20).",
    "In the current study, a large language model, ChatGPT-4, was used to perform a scientometrics analysis.",
    "Prior research has predominantly relied on techniques such as string searches, sentiment analysis, and linguistic complexity analysis (e.g., Hassan et al., 2020; Sienkiewicz & Altmann, 2016)."
  ]
}